    Lines.Strings = (
      'So, you have created a script with the Script Generator, and now you want to know how to use it?'
      ''
      'Well, fear not, it is fairly simple. In fact, there are many ways to do it.'
      ''
      'You can simply copy-and-paste the script from the Script Generator''s script window into the NWN Toolset''s script editor. Just remember to copy everything. This can be done by selecting all the text in the window then copying it (click in the window, then hit CTL-A followed by CTL-C), or with the button under the script window. The button will also give you options to save the script, compile it (if the command line compiler was found), and add it and the compiled version to a module or .erf file. (These options are also available from the "File" menu.)'
      ''
      'If your script will not compile:'
      'More than 99% of the reports Lilac Soul has had about scripts not compiling were caused by the user not copying everything. Press the button and copy everything. If it still does not compile, and your copy of NWN is patched to 1.69, please report this as a bug (The_Krit@hotmail.com).'
    )
